<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-25T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/907: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prendergast</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-25T10:00:00-04:00">April 25,
                                    1939—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. My telegram No. 16, April 24, 2 p.m. Cabinet remains unchanged.
                            Congress dissolved. Everything quiet here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Prendergast</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>